content:
Configure Performance Monitoring for a Prediction Definition

 Configure performance monitoring if you want Einstein Discovery to display performance monitoring charts for a prediction definition. 

To measure model performance, Einstein Discovery compares predicted outcomes with actual outcomes.

To configure performance monitoring:

View a prediction definition that uses automated writeback fields.
Select Monitor performance when prompted.
Select an Outcome Field to use for determining terminal state.
Specify one or more conditions:
	* Select a field
	* Select an operator (Equals or Not Equals)
	* Set a value
Filter expressions are case-sensitive. The value you specify must be an exact match.

Einstein displays object fields to which you have access. 
Click Save Settings.
title: Configure Performance Monitoring for Prediction Definitions
